    {
      "paragraph_name": "1200-SCHEDULE-PSB",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This paragraph schedules the IMS PSB. It executes a DLI SCHD command to schedule the PSB specified by PSB-NAME. If the PSB has been scheduled more than once, it first issues a DLI TERM command to terminate the PSB and then issues another DLI SCHD command. It moves the DIBSTAT value to IMS-RETURN-CODE. If the status is OK, it sets the IMS-PSB-SCHD flag to TRUE. Otherwise, it moves error information to error variables, sets the error flags, and calls 9500-LOG-ERROR to log the error.",
