    {
      "paragraph_name": "5500-READ-AUTH-SUMMRY",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This paragraph reads the pending authorization summary from the IMS database. It uses the XREF-ACCT-ID to build the key (PA-ACCT-ID) for the IMS GET UNIQUE (GU) call. The paragraph checks the IMS return code (DIBSTAT) to determine if the read was successful. If the segment is found (STATUS-OK), it sets FOUND-PAUT-SMRY-SEG to TRUE. If the segment is not found (SEGMENT-NOT-FOUND), it sets NFOUND-PAUT-SMRY-SEG to TRUE. If any other error occurs during the read, it logs a critical error message including the IMS return code to the error log. It calls 9500-LOG-ERROR to log errors.",
