      "purpose": "This paragraph performs termination tasks for the program. It first checks if the IMS PSB is scheduled (IMS-PSB-SCHD). If so, it terminates the IMS connection using EXEC DLI TERM. Then, it calls 9100-CLOSE-REQUEST-QUEUE to close the request message queue. The paragraph consumes IMS-PSB-SCHD as input. It does not produce any direct output, but triggers the IMS termination and MQ queue closure. The business logic involves ensuring that the IMS connection is terminated and the MQ queue is closed before the program ends. There is no explicit error handling within this paragraph itself; error handling is delegated to the called paragraph. It calls 9100-CLOSE-REQUEST-QUEUE to close the request message queue.",
